            "abstract": [
                {
                    "value": "The Joseph Hecht Papers (dated 1938-1945) contain one small box of letters, poetry, photographs, and memorabilia related to Joseph Hecht's military service during the Spanish Civil War and World War II. Joseph Hecht (1906-1945) was an American soldier and volunteer in the Abraham Lincoln Brigades. He was killed in action in 1945 while serving in the United States Army during World War II. The bulk of the collection includes documents related to Hecht's death in 1945 during World War II, including letters of condolences and military correspondence regarding the posthumous military honors he received. Other materials include personal items he received during his time in the Abraham Lincoln Brigades, including a wallet given to him by the Spanish War Ministry and a Communist Party of Spain membership booklet.",
                    "id": "aspace_9a477021fa86f1e58d494bc9fb5c597a"
                }
            ],
